Croatian language workshop at KNAP 2026.

Creative Croatian language workshop for adults with basic knowledge of language. We will meet once a week and learn Croatian trough supportive and funny ways talking about everyday issues. 

Workshops begin on Saturday 7th of February 2026. We will meet every Saturday at 11.00 to 12.30 in KNAP classroom, Ivaniƒágradska 41 a. We will skip 21st Feb and Saturday holidays when KNAP is closed.

Paticipants will have the optional opportunity to represent the art, food or drinks the countries they are coming from.

items.text:
Hi all!
I hope everyone is having a great week!

I'm Roisin, I'm 23 with a playing age of 16-26, based in Northamptonshire and I have bases in Bristol, Edinburgh and London. I am an actor, musician, and writer. 

I am looking to build my film showreel and connect with fellow creatives in and around the Midlands. I am interested in short films, indie projects and student films. 

Spotlight: 

https://www.spotlight.com/1019-4502-3895

Feel free to drop me a DM about any projects! 

Thanks!

Ro

items.text: We are currently casting for our upcoming virtual production of ‚ÄòKing Lear‚Äô directed by myself and colin albo. We would love to see lots of new talent, please do fill out the audition form if interested and send over your headshot/resume to the email provided. Any questions ask away below!

sharedPost.text:
AUDITION ANNOUNCEMENT

King Lear by William Shakespeare

A Virtual Staged Reading
Presented by Curtain Call Virtual Productions

Curtain Call Virtual Productions is proud to announce auditions for a virtual staged reading of William Shakespeare‚Äôs monumental tragedy King Lear.

Audition Date:
Sunday, February 22nd
7:30 p.m. BST / 2:30 p.m. EST / 11:30 a.m. PST

Held Virtually (via Zoom)

PRODUCTION TEAM
Co-Directed by: Colin Albo & Ashley Marsh

Original Script by: William Shakespeare

Edits & Language Modernization by: Colin Albo

HOW TO REGISTER
To register for auditions, participants must complete both of the following steps:

Email your headshot and theatrical r√©sum√© to

curtaincallvirtualproductions@gmail.com

Fill out the audition form linked on either the event page or the Facebook announcement

Once registration is complete, all auditioning actors will receive an email containing a PDF of the audition sides, which will be read during the audition.

No advanced preparation is required.

This is a staged reading, and multiple roles will be doubled.

All roles are open unless otherwise noted.

Please note: the role of Oswald has already been cast.

Important note: Due to the violence and mature content contained throughout the play, absolutely nobody under the age of 18 is allowed to audition! Absolutely no exceptions!

ROLES AVAILABLE
King Lear
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
The aging King of Britain whose decision to divide his kingdom based on his daughters‚Äô professions of love sets the tragedy in motion. His journey from absolute authority to madness and painful self-knowledge is the heart of the play.

Goneril
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Lear‚Äôs eldest daughter; ruthless, power-hungry, and manipulative. Married to the Duke of Albany. Embodies cruelty and ingratitude.

Regan
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Lear‚Äôs middle daughter; equally cruel, often more sadistic than Goneril. Married to the Duke of Cornwall. Acts as Goneril‚Äôs partner in stripping Lear of power and dignity.

Cordelia
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Lear‚Äôs youngest daughter; honest, principled, and loving despite her refusal to flatter him. Marries the King of France and becomes Queen of France. Represents moral truth and emotional integrity.
Doubles as: The Fool ‚Äî Lear‚Äôs companion and truth-teller who uses wit and riddles to expose harsh truths.

Gloucester
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Early 40s‚ÄìLate 60s
A nobleman whose story parallels Lear‚Äôs: a father misjudging his children. Father of Edmund and Edgar. His blinding and suffering mirror Lear‚Äôs descent into madness.

Edmund
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Gloucester‚Äôs illegitimate son; ambitious, clever, and morally corrupt. A driving antagonist whose manipulation fuels much of the play‚Äôs violence.

Edgar
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìLate 30s
Gloucester‚Äôs legitimate son; loyal, moral, and forced into disguise as ‚ÄúPoor Tom‚Äù to help his father. Represents endurance, redemption, and survival.

Albany
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Goneril‚Äôs husband. Albany begins the play restrained and politically cautious, overshadowed by stronger personalities. As the kingdom fractures, he develops a moral spine, ultimately rejecting cruelty and asserting principled leadership. Doubles as: Doctor, Knight, Curan

Cornwall
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Regan‚Äôs spouse and a ruthless enforcer of authority. Impulsive, violent, and tyrannical, Cornwall embodies unchecked authoritarianism and the danger of power without empathy. Doubles as: Gentleman, Herald, Old Man

Kent
Supporting Role | Any Gender | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
A fiercely loyal noble and trusted advisor to Lear. Blunt, principled, and courageous to the point of self-sacrifice, Kent is banished for speaking truth to power and disguises themself to continue serving Lear in exile. Doubles as: Duke of Burgundy, Messenger

Oswald (CAST)
Supporting Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Any Age
Goneril‚Äôs primary servant. Endlessly obedient, Oswald follows any and all instructions from his mistress without considering their moral implications, rendering him cruel and heartless in her shadow.
Doubles as: King of France, Servant 1

Performers of all backgrounds are encouraged to audition.

This production embraces non-traditional casting and aims to assemble a strong ensemble to explore the power, cruelty, and humanity at the heart of King Lear.

# **CASTING CALL **

Hi,

I am Pragati Gupta, seeking actors for short scenes to be filmed for a graduate film directing class at UNCW.

Here is the breakdown for the ‚ÄúSorry We Missed You‚Äù scene recreation.

*Scene brief:* When a working-class father discovers his teenage son‚Äôs quiet rebellion, the family is forced to confront the cost of survival versus the promise of a better future.

**SEB**: 15-18 yrs old, (Male, Teenage son, Actors 18+ who can convincingly play younger are welcome.)

**ABBIE**: 40-50 yrs old, (Female, Mother, Calm authority, controlled intensity)

Actors will need to be available on **Wednesday, Feb 11, from 8:30am-12pm**. The shoot location will be on the UNCW Campus.

Submit the following (headshot, acting resume, video audition) to pg7528@uncw.edu.

Subject line: ‚ÄúCharacter Name‚Äù in ‚ÄúSorry We Missed You‚Äù.

Please include-

Name:

Age:

Recent photo:

Acting resume:

Submissions must be received by the morning of **Feb 4, 2026**.

items.text:
üé¨ **CAST & CREW CALL ‚Äì INDEPENDENT THRILLER FILM (1-DAY SHOOT)**
üìç Forney, Texas | One Location | Psychological Thriller

Hi everyone ‚Äî
I‚Äôm producing and directing a contained psychological thriller titled *Unraveled Vows*, and I‚Äôm looking to collaborate with passionate actors and crew members who want to be part of something cinematic, intimate, and festival-ready.

This is a low-budget, high-quality indie film designed to be shot in one day, one house, with only 3 main characters ‚Äî very performance-driven and story-focused.

The finished film will be pitched to executives, producers, and streaming platforms, and everyone involved will receive ownership/percentage participation in the project, not just a credit.

If you want to help build something meaningful instead of just another gig, this is for you.

üé≠ **CASTING (3 Principal Roles)**

**James (Male, 30‚Äì40)**
Charismatic, calm, rising politician. Loving husband with a darker, calculated side.

**Fatima (Female, late 20s‚Äìearly 30s)**
Emotionally layered, vulnerable but strong. Carries guilt and secrets. Lead role.

**Ken (Male, 30‚Äì40)**
Charming but dangerous. Quiet, psychological menace. Intense presence.

(Strong acting ability required ‚Äì dialogue-heavy roles)

üé• **CREW NEEDED**

‚Ä¢ Camera Operator / DP
‚Ä¢ Sound Recordist / Boom Mic Owner
‚Ä¢ Editor
‚Ä¢ Sound Design / Post Audio
‚Ä¢ PA (optional)

If you own gear (camera, boom, audio equipment), huge plus.

ü§ù **What You Get**

‚Ä¢ Ownership/percentage participation in the film
‚Ä¢ IMDb credit
‚Ä¢ Festival + streaming exposure
‚Ä¢ Transportation stipend
‚Ä¢ Food provided
‚Ä¢ 1-day shoot only
‚Ä¢ Collaborative, creative environment

This is perfect for actors and filmmakers building reels, credits, and real projects.

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì JENNY & POPPY (Newcastle)** 

We are currently casting **two key female roles** for a Newcastle-based short film / pilot being produced as part of a university project.

**Roles:**

**JENNY (mid - late 20s)**
Confident, sharp, and socially switched-on. Jenny is witty, emotionally intelligent, and often the voice of reason within the group. Strong presence on screen.

**POPPY (mid - late 20s)**
Warm, expressive, and empathetic. Poppy is thoughtful and emotionally open, with a grounded and natural energy. A character with depth and subtlety.

 **Location:** Newcastle (Bar No.28 & The Last Resort)
 **Shoot dates:** First two weeks of February (starting 4th Feb) ‚Äì approx. **6 days availability required**
 **Unpaid student production** (travel support available)
 Great **showreel material + headshots provided**

Submission ends 1st February.

If interested, please get in touch:

 willm.patton@gmail.com
 07495 605757

Hallo in die Runde!

Wir drehen unseren zweiten Kurzfilm ‚ÄúCry Sam‚Äù und suchen hierf√ºr den passenden Cast.

Insgesamt zu vergeben sind 4 Rollen, davon 

3 m√§nnliche Hauptrollen (Ben, Nick & Frank) sowie
1 m√§nnliche Nebenrolle (Pablo).

Worum geht‚Äôs im Film?
Ben und Nick sitzen in der Klemme. Sie haben den Bank√ºberfall wie geplant durchgezogen aber am vereinbarten Treffpunkt taucht niemand auf. Mit zwei Geiseln an der Backe m√ºssen sie feststellen, 
dass Geld nicht alle ihre Probleme l√∂st.

Die genauen Rollenbeschreibungen, sowie weitere Infos zu unserem Projekt findet ihr im angeh√§ngten PDF.

Voraussichtlicher Drehzeitraum ist die zweite Oktoberwoche 2026.
Drehort ist der Neckar-Odenwaldkreis.

Es handelt sich um ein No-Budget-Projekt, Verpflegung am Set ist vorhanden, leider k√∂nnen wir keine Fahrtkosten und Unterkunft zahlen.

Meldet euch gerne direkt per Nachricht oder auch per Mail an katlenafilm@gmail.com

items.text:
**CASTING CALL FOR WEB SERIES**

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm seeking actors for the first episode in a comedy web series, *Vancouver I Think We Should See Other Cities*. It revolves around a young man navigating the surreal everyday life of the Canadian city.

This first episode titled ‚ÄúTurn Down The Heat‚Äù is surreal but also risqu√© in what I hope is the best way possible. It‚Äôs important to note that nothing of graphic nature is ever depicted onscreen. 

My number one priority is ensuring a welcome and safe environment where we are able to collaborate on a strong project. If you have any questions regarding the material before submitting, please DM me and I am more than happy to discuss. 

**Logline:**

A young man, Paul, goes to a meeting of the Hudson Williams Fan Club only to realize that he may be out of his depth.

**Production Details:**
* Location: Vancouver, BC
* Filming Dates: Latter half of February 2026 (TBD)
* Non-Union / Volunteer
* Food and IMDb credit provided

**ROLES**

**STEVEN - Male, Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

The charismatic leader of the Hudson Williams Fan Club.

**JULIA - Female, Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

A member of the Hudson Williams Fan Club. She is understanding and supportive to Paul when he needs it.

**HUDSON WILLIAMS FAN CLUB MEMBERS - Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

This first episode titled ‚ÄúTurn Down The Heat‚Äù is surreal but also risqu√© in what I hope is the best way possible. It‚Äôs important to note that nothing of graphic nature is ever depicted onscreen.

sharedPost.text:
I come from the gutter.

And I‚Äôve still achieved everything I set out to do so far.

It wasn‚Äôt easy, it was a struggle but I‚Äôm not here to dramatise it. 

I started with nothing. No safety net and no support. 

Everything I‚Äôve built came from my own mind, my own awareness, my own refusal to give up.

There were weeks I slept on the streets.

I‚Äôve been cold, hungry, exhausted and invisible. 

When things were at their lowest, no system showed up.

No institution came to save me and no authority stepped in.

The only thing that carried me through was faith. 

Trusting in God when there was nothing else to trust.

I‚Äôm not here to be political, I incarnated here to be honest. 

Don‚Äôt hand your life over to a group of men in suits. 

Don‚Äôt outsource your soul. 

Trust in God. 

Love your neighbour. 

Build something real.

That‚Äôs how revolutions actually start.

Jorroü™∂

items.text:
Not everyone starts this industry with money, contacts, or a foot in the door.

That‚Äôs exactly why our Agency Pack Day was created.

It began as a way to support underprivileged actors ‚Äî talented people who just needed a real opportunity, proper materials, and guidance without barriers.

That mission is still at the heart of it.

But now? It‚Äôs open to any actor who‚Äôs serious about stepping up, being seen properly, and moving forward in this industry.

Because ability shouldn‚Äôt be wasted. And opportunity should exist for those willing to act on it.

If you‚Äôre ready for the next step, get in touch and join the next Agency Pack Day.

üëâ www.mzacting.com/agency-pack.html

items.text:
Hi there üëãüèª
I‚Äôm Freya Tingley, an Australian actress reaching out to connect with filmmakers who are looking to collaborate.

My work includes Netflix‚Äôs Hemlock Grove, playing Wendy Darling on Once Upon a Time, working with Clint Eastwood on Jersey Boys, voicing a lead role in Netflix‚Äôs DOTA, and leading six feature films including the horror titles The Sonata and Time Addicts (currently streaming on Netflix).

I‚Äôm especially passionate about storytelling and horror, and I‚Äôm keen to collaborate on projects that are moving toward production ‚Äî whether proof of concept shorts, features, or series.

I can work in the US, UK, and Australia, and I‚Äôm currently based in Australia.

My showreel is available on IMDb:
imdb.me/freyatingley

Feel free to reach out ‚Äî I‚Äôd love to connect!

Freya

items.text:
Hi everyone!

I‚Äôm starting to explore entertainment companies that are remote or mostly hybrid and would love any insight. This can be in film, TV, music, sports, or any creative space.

I‚Äôm based in San Diego and own a home here, so ideally I‚Äôm looking for something that allows flexibility to go back and forth to LA when needed, but not be fully office-based.

For background, I‚Äôm a business attorney, but I‚Äôm open to roles in legal or business affairs, as well as non-legal roles where a legal background is still a strong asset.

If you know of any companies that are remote or hybrid-friendly, even if they are not hiring right now, I would be so grateful to hear about them.

topComments.text: Are you familiar enough with Entertainment law to offer consultations to Independent Producers?

**Wednesday 4th February 2026**
üìçThe Two Brewers, Clapham

Expect a mixed bill of drag, stand-up, musical theatre, live music, spoken word, pop acts and queer cabaret. You‚Äôll see established performers sharing the best of their work alongside emerging artists stepping into the spotlight with something fresh.

With cabaret-style seating, it‚Äôs social by design. Come to watch, come to meet people, come to have a big joyful night in a queer-run room. And every ticket supports Queer Theatre‚Äôs work producing LGBTQIA+ stories and nurturing LGBTQIA+ theatre-makers.

Hi,

I am a writer-director (NYFA trained) based in the NJ/NY area, prepping a 7-9 min short film blending dance, music, poetry, and quiet emotional storytelling in a contemporary Indo-American setting. 

This film is a standalone pilot for a small, short-form anthology. I am looking to connect with NJ/NY based collaborators (DOP, AD, Screenplay consultant) who are serious about craft and deeply passionate about storytelling. 

Open to collaborators of all backgrounds. Local availability and commitment are key. 

If this resonates, please DM me and I will share more details!

üé≠CASTING CALLüé≠

Greetings all! I hope you are well.

Looking for a Good Male Actor (Q) ages from 16 - 18 years for A WELL KNOWN TELENOVELA!
Shoot Date: TBC
Gender: Male (Q)
Character Breakdown: He is polite, helpful and endearingly shy. He laps up the opportunity to stay with his Father and stepmother. Beneath the soulful eyes and soft-spoken humanity lies a chillingly advanced predator, even though he is only 16 years old.  

Language: KZN ZULU (deep zulu)
Rate: TBC

You need to be able to perform. Tapes must be in KZN Zulu.

Please send me your PICTURE (HEADSHOT) AND ANY VIDEO OF YOU ACTING (MONOLOGUES ALSO ACCEPTED), upon approval you will receive CHARACTER BIO & SCRIPT to do your SELF TAPE AUDITION. 

I NEED GREAT ACTORS, NO CHANCERS PLEASE!

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) for ALL AGES, ALL DEMOGRAPHICS - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy or counselling session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. For this round of sessions we are planning both longer form scripted and shorter improv shoots.

We are currently especially interested in meeting actors who identify as queer or trans, and we are also very interested in actors who identify as Asian or latinx.

However, all ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are absolutely welcome.

All experience levels with acting are welcome. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are February 3 to February 20, based on actor availability, but our needs are ongoing and more will occur in the future, so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $60 CAD per hour, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1-2 hours. If there is some significant preparation required, compensation is offered for that time.

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you, such as gender identity, age, cultural/racial background. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

sharedPost.text:
I come from the gutter.

And I‚Äôve still achieved everything I set out to do so far.

It wasn‚Äôt easy, it was a struggle but I‚Äôm not here to dramatise it. 

I started with nothing. No safety net and no support. 

Everything I‚Äôve built came from my own mind, my own awareness, my own refusal to give up.

There were weeks I slept on the streets.

I‚Äôve been cold, hungry, exhausted and invisible. 

When things were at their lowest, no system showed up.

No institution came to save me and no authority stepped in.

The only thing that carried me through was faith. 

Trusting in God when there was nothing else to trust.

I‚Äôm not here to be political, I incarnated here to be honest. 

Don‚Äôt hand your life over to a group of men in suits. 

Don‚Äôt outsource your soul. 

Trust in God. 

Love your neighbour. 

Build something real.

sharedPost.text:
I come from the gutter.

And I‚Äôve still achieved everything I set out to do so far.

It wasn‚Äôt easy, it was a struggle but I‚Äôm not here to dramatise it. 

I started with nothing. No safety net and no support. 

Everything I‚Äôve built came from my own mind, my own awareness, my own refusal to give up.

There were weeks I slept on the streets.

I‚Äôve been cold, hungry, exhausted and invisible. 

When things were at their lowest, no system showed up.

No institution came to save me and no authority stepped in.

The only thing that carried me through was faith. 

Trusting in God when there was nothing else to trust.

I‚Äôm not here to be political, I incarnated here to be honest. 

Don‚Äôt hand your life over to a group of men in suits. 

Don‚Äôt outsource your soul. 

Trust in God. 

Love your neighbour. 

Build something real.

That‚Äôs how revolutions actually start.

Jorroü™∂

items.text:
CASTING - BLOOD & PAPER

Genre: Drama, Coming of Age

Synopsis: After a violent altercation leaves her suspended from school, anger-prone Demi becomes obsessed with obtaining her Tribal ID to prove that she belongs somewhere. But as her need to protect others pushes them farther away, she must confront the realization that identity is not something you can find on a piece of paper.

Roles:

DEMI: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Female, Black/African Descent, Racially Ambiguous, Lead)

A high schooler with anger issues, a lack of friends, but a fierce loyalty to protect those around her. None of her emotions come with a middle ground: when she‚Äôs sad, she‚Äôs inconsolable, when she‚Äôs angry, she‚Äôs furious. Ends up pushing people away due to this nature. Begins an obsessive attempt to obtain her Tribal ID in hopes that it will make her feel like she belongs somewhere.

LENA: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Female, Any Ethnicity, Supporting)

Demi‚Äôs Older Sister. Loves and cares for Demi, but secretly holds some resentment towards the problem child that is her sister. She is moving across the country for college, and is worried how Demi will do without her there.

ADRIAN: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Male, Native American/Indigenous Descent, Hispanic/Latino, Supporting)

An attractive, native farm hand, and childhood best friend of Demi. He admires her protective nature, and has always had a crush on her .. though Demi has always been too oblivious to notice.

DRUNKARDS: (20-30, Male, Any Ethnicity)

Two drunk men on the street who catcall Lena, not realizing that doing so will incur the wrath of Demi. 

Production Company: Nymesis Studios, Dir. Corinne Nuncio

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Corinne@nymesisstudios.com, please reach out with headshot and resume for sides. (If you don‚Äôt have a headshot or resume, please reach out for sides regardless)

Use BLOOD & PAPER - ROLE in your email header.

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Unpaid. Footage provided, final copy of film provided, meals provided.

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Virtual, Self Tape auditions due by Saturday, February 7th. Submit to Corinne@nymesisstudios.com. In-person callback date, early-mid February.

Shooting Schedule: Shoots 6-7 days, March 8-14. Planned rehearsal dates in late February, early March.

Filming Location: Sedalia, Denver, Aurora

Project Description: We will be shooting on a ranch around real animals (specifically horses and cows), please be aware for any possible allergies.

topComments.text: Right on! A Native American story line. I wish I fit the script.

KENT and SUSSEX AREAS
Science Boffins is currently looking for more phenomenal Science Boffins to help us to bring science to life for primary school children. We have parties, schools and events throughout the year.

You don't need a formal background in science as we teach you everything you'll need to know.

All you need is access to a car (unless London based), the ability to work some weekends/weekdays and the desire to launch rockets, concoct potions and generally share just how much fun science can be.

HOW DOES BEING A SCIENCE BOFFIN WORK?

For the right person, this could be the most fun way of making an extra income.

You'll get to enjoy inspiring and educating children, having a fantastic time and getting paid along the way. You'll travel to an event in your local area and bring science to life for primary school age children with some brilliant science experiments.

Are you a fun, enthusiastic and reliable person and able to communicate effectively and promptly to potential bookings? Then join a nationwide team of 40+ well-paid Science Boffin presenters.  We have a strong reputation, rave reviews, and the privilege of working with some globally recognised companies.

We're a friendly bunch and have a (we think!) cracking training program to help you get up to speed. If that sounds like you? You too can become one of our amazing Science Boffins and bring science alive to children.

Looking forward to hearing from you.

Annette

Science Boffins

#castingcalls #greatbritishbakeoffmusical #casting #castingcall

The Brookside Theatre are looking for the last few 'contestants' to join their amazing cast for their charity production of THE GREAT BRITISH BAKE OFF MUSICAL 

Roles:

GEMMA (Female identifying - playing age 30s) Mezzo Belt.

A carer from Blackpool

BEN (Male identifying - playing age 30s/40s) Baritone/Tenor 

A widowed police officer from Bristol; single dad to Lily 

HASSAN (Male identifying - playing age 17-25) Baritone/Tenor - Needs to rap
An A-Level Student from London (Middle Eastern Heritage)

RUSSELL (Male identifying - playing age 45-70) Baritone/Tenor - Flamboyant aeronautic engineer

DEZZA (Male identifying - playing age 25-50) Baritone/Tenor

A Vegan who lives on a houseboat

Production runs 6th - 10th May 2026

Venue: Brookside Theatre, Romford (2 mins walk from Lizzie Line / Free Parking)

Rehearsals: Monday & Wednesday evenings & Sunday daytimes by a schedule starting immediately at the theatre 

Profit Share production

If you are interested or know someone that might be right for any of these roles please get in touch either by PM or email casting@brooksidetheatre.com

**CASTING CALL ‚Äî ALT / GRUNGE GUYS ‚Äî PAID**
[ Los Angeles Locals Only ]

We're looking to cast x5 alternative/grunge guys to be part of short-form content that we are shooting for an independent artist. Not a high-budget project, but could be super cool to be a part of !!

**Date**: Tues Feb 10
**Platform**: TikTok / Instagram [ short-form shoot ]
**Role**: 'Alternative Guy'
**Location**: Indoor, Warehouse
**Compensation**: $120
**Commitment**: 2h, sometime in the afternoon
**Wardrobe**: To be coordinated with the director once you're casted.

**Apply via email *****with the following information*****:**
‚Äî Name + age range
‚Äî Location
‚Äî Recent photo
‚Äî Social media links
‚Äî Short selfie video (15-30 seconds) introducing yourself **

**Email To**: contact@meldemelo.com
**Subject**: Alt Guy Casting ‚Äî Feb 10th Short-form Shoot

*Please do not send me any other casting emails if you do not fit the casting call, as your email address will be blocked for future postings ***

items.text:
CASTING CALL: Echoes from the Abyss ‚Äì Season 1
Project Type: Narrative Audio Drama

Genre: Horror / Mystery / Anthology

Production Company: Mannequin Productions

Union Status: Non-Union

Compensation: Unpaid, Full Credit in Episode Description and Promotional Materials

Mannequin Productions is casting voice actors for principal roles in Echoes from the Abyss, a horror anthology audio drama told through recovered audio recordings, interviews, broadcasts, and firsthand accounts. Each episode stands alone, connected by a narrator who provides context and framing, allowing the stories to speak for themselves. The series focuses on documentation, memory, and how people attempt to make sense of experiences they cannot fully explain.

Actors cast in principal roles may also be asked to voice supporting or minor characters throughout the season.

Direct any questions to mannequin.productions29@gmail.com

HOW TO SUBMIT (Choose from the following methods)

üìå Casting Calls America Listing:

https://castingcalls.co/Bh4NJu

üìå Google Form:

https://forms.gle/STjRU7UfFVrPDB189

items.title: Living Room Shakespeare Co.

topComments.text:
I can‚Äôt speak for all but I was involved in a few of them during and post covid! Often it involved individually recording live performers on a zoom call, and editing them together! A great example of it that is available is what Living Room Shakespeare did during covid: https://youtube.com/@livingroomshakespeareco.8383?si=gLd_0Gu9euukLnsq

Queer Shakespeare also continues to do this format! https://youtu.be/XL0-yHdb5Fo?si=WNzvh_jXazLxqSHj

üíé Casting type can shift with ùó∞ùóºùóªùòÅùó≤ùòÖùòÅ. Archetype always shows up under ùóΩùóøùó≤ùòÄùòÄùòÇùóøùó≤.

What an incredible evening it was to be interviewed by the wonderful Victoria Beale Live with a studio audience at the 'Business Growth Crowd - Global Podcast Networking with New London media in London bridge today! 

I had the chance to share insights from my journey of standing up against the hostile infiltrations in our world while also promoting my upcoming short film premiere, 'Where are the Children?' 

The full interview is in the editing stage right now, but I wanted to share this snippet in the meantime!
....................................................................................

items.text:
**Castingaufruf f√ºr studentischen Kurzfilm (T√ºbinale)**

Meine studentische Filmgruppe sucht Darsteller*innen f√ºr einen ca. 6-min√ºtigen Kurzfilm, der im Rahmen der T√ºbinale entsteht. Gedreht wird in der Fildergegend nahe Stuttgart. Der genaue Drehzeitraum wird noch bekannt gegeben.

**Logline:**
Als eine junge Frau beginnt, ihre Beziehung mit einem anderen Paar zu vergleichen, verliert sie den Blick f√ºr die Liebe, die direkt vor ihr steht.

**Gesuchte Rollen (alle ca. 19‚Äì25 Jahre):**

**Weibliche Hauptrolle**
Junge Frau in ihrer ersten ernsthaften Beziehung. Unsicher, emotional offen, stark von √§u√üeren Erwartungen und Vergleichen beeinflusst. Die Rolle erfordert ein sensibles Spiel innerer Konflikte und leiser emotionaler Ver√§nderungen.

**M√§nnliche Hauptrolle**
Ihr Freund. Bodenst√§ndig, ruhig und bem√ºht. Er liebt ehrlich, ger√§t aber zunehmend unter Druck, weil er den Erwartungen seiner Partnerin nicht gerecht werden kann. Subtiles, zur√ºckgenommenes Spiel ist wichtig.

**Weibliche Nebenrolle**
Junge Frau mit perfekter Au√üenwirkung. Kontrolliert und diszipliniert, privat jedoch angespannt. Die Rolle lebt vom Kontrast zwischen √§u√üerer Kontrolle und innerer Unsicherheit.

**M√§nnliche Nebenrolle**
Charismatisch, dominant, stark auf Au√üenwirkung bedacht. Kontrollierend und schnell reizbar. Muss zwischen Charme und unterschwelliger Bedrohlichkeit wechseln k√∂nnen.

Schauspielerfahrung ist willkommen, aber keine Voraussetzung. Wichtig sind Verl√§sslichkeit, Lust auf Spielen und Interesse an einem emotionalen, beziehungszentrierten Stoff.
Bei Interesse einfach eine Nachricht schreiben, dann schicken wir weitere Infos und das Drehbuch.

üé¨ DENVER / AURORA FILMMAKERS ‚Äî VOLUNTEER CREW CALL (IMDb CREDIT) üé¨
I‚Äôm filming a documentary in Lyons, CO on Monday, February 9, and I‚Äôm looking for a small volunteer crew‚Äîespecially a Director of Photography‚Äîto help capture an important story.

This film has been built entirely by volunteers‚Äîpeople who believe stories can actually change systems. We‚Äôre keeping the crew small, intentional, and respectful of everyone‚Äôs time.

### üé• Roles Needed:

‚Ä¢ Director of Photography (priority)  

‚Ä¢ Assistant Camera (AC)  

‚Ä¢ Lighting / Gaffer  

‚Ä¢ Production Assistant (PA)

### üìç Shoot Details:

üìÖ Monday, Feb 9  

üìç Anschutz Medical Campus ‚Äì Aurora, CO  

üéû Documentary (mental health, prevention, community)  

üé¨ IMDb credit provided  

‚è± Short, focused shoot day

This project centers on mental health prevention, belonging, and real human stories‚Äînot spectacle, not fluff. If you‚Äôre a DP or crew member who cares about purpose-driven filmmaking, meaningful collaboration, and telling stories that actually matter, I‚Äôd love to connect.

Please comment or DM with:

‚Ä¢ The role you‚Äôre interested in  

‚Ä¢ A link to your work, reel, or IG (if you have one)

Even sharing this with someone in your network helps more than you know.  

Thank you üíô

items.text:
Title: Saturdays

Genre: Thriller/Comedy

Logline: After accidentally taking a new designer drug on the way to a Halloween party, three broke nobodies become viral vigilantes in a city on the edge but their rise to infamy puts them in the cross-hairs of a charismatic cartel leader.

Role:

Dave (30-50) Unkillable, unshakable, and possibly unmedicated. Somehow still endearing. Dave is an uber driver, a hype man, and a secret weapon and comes from a different era. He‚Äôs the uncle at thanksgiving that you hope didn‚Äôt bring a bottle of scotch (you know he did). A chaotic wildcard who might be a genius... or just very, very lucky.

Production Type: Indie

Production Company: Loste Films

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Feature

Compensation: Catering/Crafty provided during proof of concept shoot. Compensation for future shoot dates is open to negotiation.

Audition Information: Send an email with headshot, resume and reel. The first round of auditions will be self-tape, then we will have in-person callbacks (downtown Denver area).

Shooting Schedule: Late February. Other shoot dates TBD

Filming Location: Highlands Ranch and Denver area

Project Description: Saturdays is an upcoming feature film we‚Äôre currently shooting the beginning of to use as a proof of concept. The scenes in the proof of concept are still being used in the final movie, which will be shot later on in the year. Due to scheduling conflicts we had to recast this role and are looking for someone who can carry mystery, comedy, and spiritual invincibility. There‚Äôs also lots of room for improv in the role. Some character inspirations include Erlich Eachman (Silicon Valley), Frank Reynolds (It‚Äôs Always Sunny), Red (Pineapple Express), Jay (Clerks), The Dude (The Big Lebowski). Attached pictures are the location/vehicles we have locked in for the first scene you‚Äôll be shooting with us.

IMDB Link: [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39423188/](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39423188/)

üé§ *CASTING CALL* | PROFESSIONAL ON-SCREEN FEMALE PRESENTER
Required For |

Event: Wedding Exhibition Fair by Asiana Magazine

Where: üìç London, UK 

Date: Sunday 8th February 2026

Call Time Arrival and Wrap Time: 1:00PM till 4:00PM

K.A Global Production House is seeking a confident, bubbly, and professional Female Presenter to host interviews and provide news-style coverage at the Wedding Exhibition Fair organised by popular Royal Fashion Brand 'Asiana'. Interviewing the Exhibitors and briefly chatting to them asking them what their Brand/Business is about. 

This opportunity is ideal for those who are passionate about Fashion and Arts who want to build or expand their on-camera portfolio. At the function you are welcome to network for your own benefit which there will be high value individuals and groups from various professional backgrounds.

We also have lot's more functions coming up such as a private Charity Event taking place on 14th February 2026 and many other functions and projects. Which we will require a Presenter.

WHO WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR?

Ages: 20's OR 30's

Fluent in English with strong voice projection

Naturally confident, energetic, and camera-friendly

Must be already based in London, UK or anyone who will be in London on that date and time

Interested in building experience, portfolio, credentials and industry connections

PLATFORM DISTRIBUTION |

Content Will Be Released On:

- Social Media Platforms

- YouTube

- K.A Global Homepage

Some Highlighted clips may be seen on South Asian Desi Television Network

WHAT YOU‚ÄôLL GAIN?

Added to K.A Global Casting Database

Support in building a professional portfolio

Introductions to Agents and Agency contacts

Consideration for future K.A Global projects, events and presenting roles

Opportunity to be considered as a Brand Ambassador

HOW TO APPLY?

Inbox The Following:

- Full Name

- Social Media Handles

- Portfolio 'If You Own One'

- Contact Information

Shortlisted applicants will receive a 5-minute phone call to discuss the event, interview style, and details.

SERIOUS APPLICANTS ONLY

Confirmed applicants for the 8th February event will be contacted Saturday morning (day before event).

The applicants not selected for this date may be contacted in advance for our 14th February 2026 Charity Event.

We are actively scouting long-term talents for upcoming projects and functions to join our team. We take Pride in those who have potential.

K.A Global ¬©

Building Creative Futures

Homepage: https://kaglobalofficial.blogspot.com/2025/04/kaglobalhomepage.html

items.text:
üé¨ URGENT CASTING CALL ‚Äì DIASPORA SHORT FILM 

ROLE: THE PHOTOGRAPHER

We are currently casting for one remaining role in our short narrative film Diaspora, being developed and produced as part of our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Set in 1970s Britain, Diaspora follows a newly migrated Cypriot man applying for a British passport. His encounter with a Balkan-born photographer becomes the emotional core of the film, as both men are forced to confront memories of displacement, identity, and belonging. The story is intimate and character-driven, set largely within a photography studio, and relies on quiet tension, emotional restraint, and subtle performance.

We are looking to cast The Photographer, a Balkan or Eastern European man (playing age approximately 50s‚Äì70s) who has settled in Britain after leaving his homeland. The character is reserved, guarded, and shaped by lived experience. Acting experience is welcome but not essential; we are primarily interested in authenticity, presence, and emotional truth.

DETAILS:
- Shooting is scheduled for 22nd‚Äì26th February in Bristol
- Availability across these dates is required
- Applicants should be based in or able to stay locally in Bristol or nearby
- This is an unpaid student project, with travel expenses and food covered

The film is intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

To apply, please send a headshot and brief CV to diasporafilm2026@gmail.com

If this role isn‚Äôt right for you personally, we‚Äôd really appreciate any shares with those who might be interested.

**CASTING CALL - PLEASE SHARE**
THE SECRET DIARY OF ADRIAN MOLE AGED 13 ¬æ 

SEEKING MIDLANDS BASED ACTORS AGED 17 ‚Äì 19 FOR ROLES IN A MAJOR NEW 9-PART BBC SERIES WRITTEN BY DAVID NICHOLLS (ONE DAY), BASED ON THE MUCH-LOVED NOVEL BY SUE TOWNSEND.

We encourage suggestions from all ethnicities, and we are open to both professional and non-professional actors and those with no prior acting experience. The characters are an eclectic group of students at a local comprehensive in 1980s Leicestershire and we are keen to see interesting, unconventional teens with character and attitude. 

If interested, please email the casting director Robert Sterne at casting@robertsterne.co.uk 

PLEASE NOTE, TO APPLY YOU MUST HAVE FINISHED YOUR GCSEs

Please provide your name, age, location and a passport style photograph.

Please mark the subject line of the email: 

CASTING CALL ‚ÄòBBC SERIES ‚Äì MIDLANDS‚Äô

THE DEADLINE FOR SUBMISSIONS IS WEDNESDAY 11TH FEBRUARY

We look forward to receiving your submissions.

**TV PRODUCER **

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

**** We cannot dispute anything against councils or large organisations - this would be a person to person / business claims****
